BN254 (alt_bn128) + Poseidon — src/vex_crypto/bn254/ (Phase 2, 2026-07-11)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

The BN254 group ops (G1/G2 add, scalar-mul, compress/decompress), the optimal-ate
pairing, and the Poseidon-BN254 hash are VEXOR'S OWN implementation. They run
INSIDE transaction execution (the sol_alt_bn128_group_op / sol_alt_bn128_compress
/ sol_poseidon syscalls), feeding account state → bank_hash, so every output is
byte-exact-gated against Firedancer Ballet and the published solana-bn254 v3.2.1 /
Firedancer test vectors (src/vex_crypto/bn254/kat.zig, `zig build test-vex-bn254`).

4. BN254 base field Fp — src/vex_crypto/bn254/fiat_fp.zig
--------------------------------------------------------
    Project : fiat-crypto
    Source  : https://github.com/mit-plv/fiat-crypto
    License : MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD-1-Clause (tri-licensed)

The ONE component carried as-is: the word-by-word Montgomery reduction for the
BN254 base-field prime, a machine-generated, formally-verified fiat-crypto Coq
extraction. Bit-identical modular reduction is mandatory for consensus, and the
canonical way to obtain it is the fiat-crypto artifact — not a hand-rolled
reduction. This is a mathematical artifact, identical regardless of who runs the
extractor; the same generator output is used by Sig and other Solana clients.
The verbatim generator banner is retained at the top of the file.

5. BN254 tower / groups / pairing / serialization — Vexor's own
---------------------------------------------------------------
Vexor-authored, informed by the framework and algorithms of:
    - Syndica's Sig  (Apache-2.0) — https://github.com/syndica/sig
      (shared/crypto/bn254: field tower shape, group law, pairing structure)
    - Firedancer Ballet (Apache-2.0) — the alt_bn128 syscall byte contract, the
      subgroup-check semantics (G2 add = curve-only, G2 mul / pairing = subgroup),
      and (during development, via a -Dballet_bn254 flag removed 2026-07-12
      once the epoch-boundary soak passed) the differential oracle used to
      byte-verify this implementation.
    - solana-bn254 v3.2.1 / ark-bn254 (Apache-2.0) — the authoritative Agave
      wire/serialization/error semantics (endianness, flag bytes, length rules).
The Fp2/Fp6/Fp12 tower, G1/G2 group law, Miller loop, final exponentiation, and
point (de)serialization were written fresh against the standard published
algorithms (references cited inline) — cleaner and reorganized, math identical,
gated byte-for-byte. We do NOT claim "from scratch, no reference."

6. Poseidon-BN254 — src/vex_crypto/bn254/poseidon.zig + poseidon_params.zig
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Vexor-authored permutation over the BN254 scalar field. The round constants (ark)
and MDS matrices originate from light-poseidon v0.2.0 / circomlib v2.0.5
(bn254_x5); they were taken from Firedancer's fd_poseidon_params.c and converted
out of Fr-Montgomery form to normal residues by src/vex_crypto/bn254/gen_poseidon_params.py
(normal = mont · R⁻¹ mod r), so the permutation runs in plain Fr arithmetic with
byte-identical output. The conversion + permutation are proven end-to-end by the
differential gate against the Firedancer/solana Poseidon vectors.
    - light-poseidon v0.2.0 (Apache-2.0) — https://github.com/Lightprotocol/light-poseidon
    - circomlib v2.0.5 (GPL-3.0, parameters/spec reference) — https://github.com/iden3/circomlib
    - Firedancer Ballet (Apache-2.0) — parameter source + differential oracle.


